boohai
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a remote place or district;  the backblocks

[perhaps from North Auckland township of Puhoi]; up the boohai: confused, wrong, messy
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: cf. backblocks, bush, cactus, wo(o)p-wo(o)ps.
Pronunciation:
Notes: up the boohai/booaye/boo-eye/booay is out of place, confused
